My family, friends and I have patronized this restaurant often and have often referred others to enjoy a meal there however my visit yesterday was unexceptionable. I decided to enjoy a lunch alone as I work in the area. I sat at the bar ordered a drink and the Asian steak salad which has always been one of my favorites. Mid way eating my salad there was plastic about three inches long in my salad! I asked the bartender/ waitress to come to me discretely as there were two other customers sitting eating lunch by themselves also, one to my left and other to my right. I didn’t want to make a show of it as I’m a fellow business owner myself and know things happen. When I called the waitress she was literally 3 feet away from me delivering a soup to a woman next to me but instead of coming to me she decided to walk the opposite way and address me from behind the bar. I then pull the plastic out of my salad and of course the people next to me witness this. The waitress apologized. I even said bag the rest to go. She removed the salad. Minutes later she returns and said they are going to make me a whole new salad. I thought wow that is nice. I asked for the check as I was leaving anyway. Would you believe they charged me for the salad! $39.19 for my drink and a salad that had plastic in it?  As to not make a scene I paid and left. Needless to say horrible way of doing business and service. You decide if you want to dine here.

Someone switched the total of my actual amount to a new figure and thought I wouldn't notice. I called the business repeatedly and contacted them on social media, but got no response. I couldn't go back to the restaurant as I don't live in NY. I had to start a claim with my back. Ponty did not work with them to resolve the issue.  There are sinister scammers at this business! I'm sorry I was not able to find out what business association, if any, Ponty is a part of so I can report them!
